{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b2ceb41-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s448"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"448"},"text":"§ 448.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Return of permit; penalty for failure to return","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Every permit issued in accordance with the provisions of sections 443 to 448 of this title, which may not be taken up by an inspector or deputy inspector, shall be returned within four days after issuance to the office of the supervisor of the harbor; such permit shall bear an indorsement by the master of the towboat, or the person acting in such capacity, stating whether the permit has been used, and, if so, the time and place of dumping. Any person violating the provisions of this section shall be liable to a fine of not more than $500 nor less than $100.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b2ceb42-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1888-06-29/ch496/s3"},"text":"June 29, 1888, ch. 496, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/25/209"},"text":"25 Stat. 209","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1894-08-18/ch299/s3"},"text":"Aug. 18, 1894, ch. 299, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/28/360"},"text":"28 Stat. 360","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1908-05-28/ch212/s8"},"text":"May 28, 1908, ch. 212, § 8","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/428"},"text":"35 Stat. 428","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b2ceb43-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b2ceb44-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6b2ceb45-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 443 to 448 of this title, referred to in text, were in the original “this section of this Act”, meaning section 3 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1888-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 1888","children":[],"tail":", which enacted sections 443 to 448 of this title. The provision of section 3 relating to issuance of permits is classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s443"},"text":"section 443 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id6b2ceb46-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of section 3 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1888-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 1888","children":[],"tail":". Said section 3 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1888-06-29"},"text":"June 29, 1888","children":[],"tail":" enacted sections 443 to 448 of this title. See Codification note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s443"},"text":"section 443 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
